  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 2cbaeec8dbe84e069925173ac3a6210b, type: 3}
  m_Name: Dlg_Ruins_Guardian_Riddle
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ElementalAlchemist.Dialogue.DialogueData
  _speaker: Ruins Guardian
  _lines:
  - You stand among the bones of an age that wanted to live forever. They reached for one thing above all others, and it unmade them.
  - It is the stone that is not a stone, the hardest and purest form the deep can yield, wedded to the draught that holds death at bay.
  - Bring me that diamond of perfect crystal, married to the elixir of unending life, and you will hold what every alchemist has died chasing.
  - Make it, and return to me. The Fragment of Soul waits behind your answer.
